46 template <typename Result, typename Left, typename Right, typename Scalar>
47 class ContractReduceBase {
48  public:
49  typedef ContractReduceBase<Result, Left, Right, Scalar>
50  ContractReduceBase_;
51  typedef const Left& first_argument_type;
52  typedef const Right& second_argument_type;
53  typedef Result result_type;
54  typedef Scalar scalar_type;
55 
56  private:
57  struct Impl {
58  Impl(const madness::cblas::CBLAS_TRANSPOSE left_op,
59  const madness::cblas::CBLAS_TRANSPOSE right_op,
60  const scalar_type alpha, const unsigned int result_rank,
61  const unsigned int left_rank, const unsigned int right_rank,
62  const Permutation& perm = Permutation())
63  : gemm_helper_(left_op, right_op, result_rank, left_rank, right_rank),
64  alpha_(alpha),
65  perm_(perm) {}
66 
67  math::GemmHelper gemm_helper_;
68  scalar_type alpha_;
69  Permutation perm_;
71  };
73 
74  std::shared_ptr<Impl> pimpl_;
75 
76  public:
77  // Compiler generated defaults are fine
78 
79  ContractReduceBase() = default;
80  ContractReduceBase(const ContractReduceBase_&) = default;
81  ContractReduceBase(ContractReduceBase_&&) = default;
82  ~ContractReduceBase() = default;
83  ContractReduceBase_& operator=(const ContractReduceBase_&) = default;
84  ContractReduceBase_& operator=(ContractReduceBase_&&) = default;
85 
87 
96  ContractReduceBase(const madness::cblas::CBLAS_TRANSPOSE left_op,
97  const madness::cblas::CBLAS_TRANSPOSE right_op,
98  const scalar_type alpha, const unsigned int result_rank,
99  const unsigned int left_rank,
100  const unsigned int right_rank,
101  const Permutation& perm = Permutation())
102  : pimpl_(std::make_shared<Impl>(left_op, right_op, alpha, result_rank,
103  left_rank, right_rank, perm)) {}
104

111  }

117  TA_ASSERT(pimpl_);

119  }

172 template <typename Result, typename Left, typename Right, typename Scalar>
173 class ContractReduce : public ContractReduceBase<Result, Left, Right, Scalar> {
174  public:
175  typedef ContractReduce<Result, Left, Right, Scalar>
176  ContractReduce_;
177  typedef ContractReduceBase<Result, Left, Right, Scalar>
178  ContractReduceBase_;
179  typedef typename ContractReduceBase_::first_argument_type
180  first_argument_type;
181  typedef typename ContractReduceBase_::second_argument_type
182  second_argument_type;
183  typedef Result result_type;
184  typedef Scalar scalar_type;
185 
186  // Compiler generated defaults are fine. N.B. this is shallow-copy.
187 
188  ContractReduce() = default;
189  ContractReduce(const ContractReduce_&) = default;
190  ContractReduce(ContractReduce_&&) = default;
191  ~ContractReduce() = default;
192  ContractReduce_& operator=(const ContractReduce_&) = default;
193  ContractReduce_& operator=(ContractReduce_&&) = default;
194 
196 
205  ContractReduce(const madness::cblas::CBLAS_TRANSPOSE left_op,
206  const madness::cblas::CBLAS_TRANSPOSE right_op,
207  const scalar_type alpha, const unsigned int result_rank,
208  const unsigned int left_rank, const unsigned int right_rank,
209  const Permutation& perm = Permutation())
210  : ContractReduceBase_(left_op, right_op, alpha, result_rank, left_rank,
211  right_rank, perm) {}
212 
214 
216  result_type operator()() const { return result_type(); }
217 
219  result_type operator()(const result_type& temp) const {
220  using TiledArray::empty;
221  TA_ASSERT(!empty(temp));
222 
223  if (!ContractReduceBase_::perm()) return temp;
224 
225  TiledArray::Permute<result_type, result_type> permute;
226  return permute(temp, ContractReduceBase_::perm());
227  }
228 
230 
235  void operator()(result_type& result, const result_type& arg) const {
236  using TiledArray::add_to;
237  add_to(result, arg);
238  }
239 
241 
247  void operator()(result_type& result, first_argument_type left,
248  second_argument_type right) const {
249  using TiledArray::empty;
250  using TiledArray::gemm;
251  if (empty(result))
252  result = gemm(left, right, ContractReduceBase_::factor(),
253  ContractReduceBase_::gemm_helper());
254  else
255  gemm(result, left, right, ContractReduceBase_::factor(),
256  ContractReduceBase_::gemm_helper());
257  }
258 
259 }; // class ContractReduce

267 template <typename Result, typename Left, typename Right>
268 class ContractReduce<Result, Left, Right,
269  TiledArray::detail::ComplexConjugate<void> >
270  : public ContractReduceBase<Result, Left, Right,
271  TiledArray::detail::ComplexConjugate<void> > {
272  public:
273  typedef ContractReduce<Result, Left, Right,

277  TiledArray::detail::ComplexConjugate<void> >
278  ContractReduceBase_;
279  typedef typename ContractReduceBase_::first_argument_type
280  first_argument_type;
281  typedef typename ContractReduceBase_::second_argument_type
282  second_argument_type;
283  typedef decltype(gemm(std::declval<Left>(), std::declval<Right>(), 1,
284  std::declval<math::GemmHelper>()))
285  result_type;
286  typedef TiledArray::detail::ComplexConjugate<void> scalar_type;
287 
288  // Compiler generated defaults are fine. N.B. This has shallow copy semantics.
289 
290  ContractReduce() = default;
291  ContractReduce(const ContractReduce_&) = default;
292  ContractReduce(ContractReduce_&&) = default;
293  ~ContractReduce() = default;
294  ContractReduce_& operator=(const ContractReduce_&) = default;
295  ContractReduce_& operator=(ContractReduce_&&) = default;
296 
298 
307  ContractReduce(const madness::cblas::CBLAS_TRANSPOSE left_op,
308  const madness::cblas::CBLAS_TRANSPOSE right_op,
309  const scalar_type alpha, const unsigned int result_rank,
310  const unsigned int left_rank, const unsigned int right_rank,
311  const Permutation& perm = Permutation())
312  : ContractReduceBase_(left_op, right_op, alpha, result_rank, left_rank,
313  right_rank, perm) {}
314 
316 
318  result_type operator()() const { return result_type(); }
319 
321  result_type operator()(result_type& temp) const {
322  using TiledArray::empty;
323  TA_ASSERT(!empty(temp));
324 
325  if (!ContractReduceBase_::perm()) {
326  using TiledArray::conj_to;
327  return conj_to(temp);
328  }
329 
330  using TiledArray::conj;
331  return conj(temp, ContractReduceBase_::perm());
332  }
333 
335 
340  void operator()(result_type& result, const result_type& arg) const {
341  using TiledArray::add_to;
342  add_to(result, arg);
343  }
344 
346 
352  void operator()(result_type& result, first_argument_type left,
353  second_argument_type right) const {
354  using TiledArray::empty;
355  using TiledArray::gemm;
356  if (empty(result))
357  result = gemm(left, right, 1, ContractReduceBase_::gemm_helper());
358  else
359  gemm(result, left, right, 1, ContractReduceBase_::gemm_helper());
360  }
361 
362 }; // class ContractReduce
